The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Liverpool ease into final

Yokohama: Liverpool eased past Costa Ricas Deportivo Saprissa 3-0 in the Fifa World Club Championship semi-final Thursday as the European champions kept a clean sheet for the 11th successive match. 

Rafael Benitezs side will now meet Brazils Sao Paulo in Sundays final with the South Americans looking for their third world title and Liverpool their first. 

Peter Crouch scored twice and captain Steven Gerrard was also on target as the European champions set a new club record of 11 successive clean sheets in all competitons. 

The final will be played at the same venue. 

Liverpool took control in the second minute when Crouch scored after being set up by John Arne Riise. Gerrard added a second in the 32nd minute, volleying another Riise delivery superbly from 20 metres. Crouch pounced on a defensive error to slide home his second in the 58th. 

